    "result": "愿意进入中高价市场的前提是获得明显不同的任务能力：非廉价听感、连续点歌、个性化调音和主持家庭或半专业活动。",
    "original": "Not cheap but worth it\nSo we wanted to upgrade the karaoke machine that we have had for a few years now. It was a pretty inexpensive machine that didn’t do a whole lot. So we saw this on sale and figured we would try it out. We found another that was a little cheaper and figured we’d get both and pick the better of the two. This system arrived first and all I can say is holy crap. This could easily be set up to use as a professional karaoke system if you wanted a second income. The sound is crisp and clear with plenty of bass. Doesn’t in any way sound “tinny” or cheap like most others might. This is the 600w version by the way. The fact that you can use your mobile device to browse the tens of thousands of songs while someone else is singing is great. You can just set up a playlist and just keep going. It’s also really nice that everyone can change the pitch or the tempo themselves if they want. The last thing is the music selection. First off for most every song I’ve heard so far  has been a pretty high quality recording. Not like some karaoke versions you get that sound like they were done on a cheap keyboard/midi system. Also I don’t think I’ve found a song yet that hasn’t been available. Even some fairly obscure songs.Anyway, while this isn’t cheap it’s worth the investment if you like to have a family song night or again would like to host your own karaoke night somewhere.",
    "translation": "不便宜，但值得\n我们想升级已经用了几年的卡拉OK机。旧机器相当便宜，能做的事情不多。看到这台促销后，我们决定试试；同时还找到另一台更便宜的机器，于是打算两台都买，再选更好的。这套系统先到，我只能说太令人惊讶了。如果愿意发展第二份收入，它完全可以搭成专业卡拉OK系统。声音清晰，有足够的低音，完全没有许多产品那种单薄、廉价的听感。这是600W版本。有人唱歌时，其他人可以用移动设备浏览数以万计的歌曲，这一点很好；可以先建播放列表，让活动持续进行。每个人还可以按需要调整音调或速度。最后是音乐选择：目前听过的大多数歌曲录音质量都很高，不像一些便宜键盘或MIDI制作的卡拉OK版本。我似乎还没有遇到找不到的歌，包括一些相当冷门的歌曲。总之，这台不便宜，但如果你喜欢家庭唱歌之夜，或者想在其他地方主持自己的卡拉OK活动，它值得投资。",
