    "original": "Good machine\nKaraoke machines have changed a lot over time. Gone are the days when you could purchase a storage device that contained a catalog of songs that YOU selected. Now we're forced to subscribe to services that aren't exactly cheap.That said, I've found this machine to be really nice; good mic quality, great sound quality, good control interface, and good battery life for portable use. The built-in display is very good, bit being about the size of an iPad means you have to be right on top of the machine to see it clearly. I especially appreciated the complimentary 6-month subscription to Karafun.For cons, it was a bit of a pain to connect it to a larger display as Wi-Fi, Bluetooth and an HDMI port (cable not included) are the only options, and they depend on your TV and local network to work. Add-ng a DVI port would help. Searching for songs via the YouTube platform is a bit clunky, but being able to use a mic for voice searching helps.All-in-all, though, I've been very pleased with this device",
