    "original": "Not very professional amplifying machine\nIt was quite easy to set up because you just need to turn the system on and press the Bluetooth button to set up wi-fi using your wi-fi password.  Then once your wi-fi is set up then you can use YouTube to search for the songs you want to sing.  The machine also has Spotify platform and Karafun also .  However if you want to sing karaoke with the words showing on the screen you have to subscribe to Spotify or Karafun.  You would have to pay the subscription price $10.00/month.  If you don’t want to pay then you can only use YouTube songs for free.  I really thought that the machine has stored some karaoke songs already for use .  However, this is not the case.  You really need to pay a subscription fee in order to sing karaoke songs properly.  So if you don’t mind using YouTube with advertisements and limited to certain songs it can be good for practice on your own.  However if you plan to have a real karaoke party with lyrics showing on the screen and the singer’s voice blocked except for the musical background accompaniment, then you need to subscribe to Spotify or Karafun and you should hook up the karaoke machine to your TV monitor with a cable.  So I am quite disappointed because I pay over $300 for the machine when I could have bought the cheaper one for a little over$100.  So if you just want to practice singing on your own just buy the $100 one.  It would probably serve the purpose.",
